---
import PageLayout from "@layouts/PageLayout.astro";
---

<PageLayout
  title="Accessibility Statement"
  description="GovCompass accessibility statement. Our commitment to WCAG 2.1 AA and making political education usable for everyone."
>
  <h1 class="font-heading text-3xl font-bold text-text-primary mb-6">
    Accessibility Statement
  </h1>

  <div class="space-y-6 text-text-secondary leading-relaxed">
    <p>
      <strong class="text-text-primary">Last updated:</strong> June 2026
    </p>

    <p>
      GovCompass exists to make South Africa's government legible to everyone, so
      the site itself needs to be usable by everyone. We are committed to meeting
      the <strong class="text-text-primary"
        >Web Content Accessibility Guidelines (WCAG) 2.1, Level AA</strong
      >, and we treat accessibility as a requirement, not an afterthought.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      What we do
    </h2>

    <p>
      We have built the following into the site to support people using
      assistive technology, keyboards, and a range of devices and connections:
    </p>

    <ul class="list-disc pl-6 space-y-2">
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Keyboard navigation:</strong> All
        interactive elements can be reached and used with a keyboard, with a
        visible focus indicator and a "skip to content" link at the top of every
        page.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Semantic structure:</strong> Pages use
        proper landmarks (header, navigation, main, footer) and a logical
        heading order, so screen readers can announce and navigate content
        correctly.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Language and labels:</strong> The site
        declares South African English (<code>lang="en-ZA"</code>), and
        interactive controls carry descriptive labels and ARIA attributes where
        needed.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Colour and contrast:</strong> Text and
        interface colours are chosen to meet AA contrast ratios, and the site is
        readable without relying on colour alone.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Readable, responsive layout:</strong>
        Content reflows cleanly down to small mobile screens, supports browser
        zoom and larger text, and is optimised to load quickly on slower
        connections.
      </li>
      <li>
        <strong class="text-text-primary">Descriptive links and images:</strong>
        Links describe where they lead, and meaningful images include
        alternative text.
      </li>
    </ul>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      How we check
    </h2>

    <p>
      Accessibility is tested as part of our build process. Every change runs
      through automated accessibility and quality checks (including Lighthouse
      accessibility audits, which must score at least 95%) and structural tests
      that verify landmarks, headings, language, and skip-link behaviour before
      anything is published.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Known limitations
    </h2>

    <p>
      We aim for full WCAG 2.1 AA conformance, but accessibility is ongoing work.
      Automated testing cannot catch everything, and some older content or
      embedded material may not yet fully meet our target. Where we identify
      gaps, we prioritise fixing them.
    </p>

    <h2 class="font-heading text-xl font-bold text-text-primary pt-4">
      Tell us if something doesn't work
    </h2>

    <p>
      If you encounter a barrier using GovCompass — a page you cannot read with a
      screen reader, a control you cannot reach with a keyboard, or anything else
      that gets in your way — please tell us. Your feedback directly helps us
      improve.
    </p>

    <p>
      Reach us via our
      <a
        href="/contact"
        class="text-compass-green underline hover:text-compass-green-dark transition-colors"
        >contact form</a
      >. Please describe the problem, the page it happened on, and the device or
      assistive technology you were using, so we can reproduce and fix it.
    </p>
  </div>
</PageLayout>
